  "explanations": [
    {
      "id": "exp_0001_v1",
      "questionId": "q_0001",
      "origin": "ai",
      "bodyEn": "This statement is true. At an uncontrolled intersection, the basic rule is to yield to traffic approaching from your right unless a sign, signal, or road marking changes that priority.",
      "sourceDerived": false,
      "aiModel": "gpt-5",
      "aiPromptVersion": "exp-v1",
      "createdBy": "codex",
      "createdAt": "2026-03-11T12:18:00Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-03-11T12:19:00Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "exp_0002_v1",
      "questionId": "q_0002",
      "origin": "ai",
      "bodyEn": "This is false. Stopping or parking close to a crosswalk reduces visibility and endangers pedestrians, so the law restricts stopping within 5 meters before a crosswalk unless a specific exception applies.",
      "sourceDerived": false,
      "aiModel": "gpt-5",
      "aiPromptVersion": "exp-v1",
      "createdBy": "codex",
      "createdAt": "2026-03-11T12:29:00Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-03-11T12:30:00Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "exp_0003_v1",
      "questionId": "q_0003",
      "origin": "manual",
      "bodyEn": "This is true. At a railroad crossing in Japan, you are required to stop just before the tracks and confirm safety, even when the warning device is silent and the gate is open.",
      "sourceDerived": false,
      "createdBy": "content-editor",
      "createdAt": "2026-03-11T12:36:00Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-03-11T12:37:00Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "exp_0004_v1",
      "questionId": "q_0004",
      "origin": "source",
      "bodyEn": "The correct answer is the red circular sign with a white horizontal bar. It means vehicles must not enter from that direction.",
      "sourceDerived": true,
      "createdBy": "source-import",
      "createdAt": "2026-03-11T12:44:00Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-03-11T12:45:00Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "exp_0005_v1",
      "questionId": "q_0005",
      "origin": "manual",
      "bodyEn": "This is false. Entering the intersection first does not let you cut off an oncoming vehicle that is continuing straight. When you turn right, you must not obstruct that vehicle.",
      "sourceDerived": true,
      "createdBy": "passdrive-editorial",
      "createdAt": "2026-03-12T01:17:00Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-03-12T01:18:00Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "exp_0006_v1",
      "questionId": "q_0006",
      "origin": "manual",
      "bodyEn": "This is true. A stop sign requires a full stop at the stop line, or just before the intersection if no stop line is present.",
      "sourceDerived": true,
      "createdBy": "passdrive-editorial",
      "createdAt": "2026-03-12T01:22:00Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-03-12T01:23:00Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "exp_0007_v1",
      "questionId": "q_0007",
      "origin": "manual",
      "bodyEn": "This is true. Before a level crossing, stop before the crossing or stop line and confirm safety to both sides. If traffic lights control the crossing, follow those lights.",
      "sourceDerived": true,
      "createdBy": "passdrive-editorial",
      "createdAt": "2026-03-12T01:26:00Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-03-12T01:27:00Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "exp_0008_v1",
      "questionId": "q_0008",
      "origin": "manual",
      "bodyEn": "This is false. The driver must make sure passengers in both the front and rear seats wear seat belts, not only the people in front.",
      "sourceDerived": true,
      "createdBy": "passdrive-editorial",
      "createdAt": "2026-03-12T01:30:00Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-03-12T01:31:00Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "exp_0009_v1",
      "questionId": "q_0009",
      "origin": "manual",
      "bodyEn": "This is false. Street parking can still be a violation even for a short time. If you leave the car and cannot drive it away immediately, it may count as abandoned parking.",
      "sourceDerived": true,
      "createdBy": "passdrive-editorial",
      "createdAt": "2026-03-12T01:34:00Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-03-12T01:35:00Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "exp_0010_v1",
      "questionId": "q_0010",
      "origin": "manual",
      "bodyEn": "This is true. If front-end parking is designated, you must follow that instruction. In residential areas it helps reduce exhaust and noise toward nearby homes.",
      "sourceDerived": true,
      "createdBy": "passdrive-editorial",
      "createdAt": "2026-03-12T01:38:00Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-03-12T01:39:00Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "exp_0011_v1",
      "questionId": "q_0011",
      "origin": "manual",
      "bodyEn": "This is false. Accessible parking spaces are reserved for drivers with physical disabilities and must not be used by regular vehicles, even briefly.",
      "sourceDerived": true,
      "createdBy": "passdrive-editorial",
      "createdAt": "2026-03-12T01:42:00Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-03-12T01:43:00Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "exp_0012_v1",
      "questionId": "q_0012",
      "origin": "manual",
      "bodyEn": "This is true. Without a posted limit, regular automobiles must follow the default limit of 60 km/h on ordinary roads.",
      "sourceDerived": true,
      "createdBy": "passdrive-editorial",
      "createdAt": "2026-03-12T01:46:00Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-03-12T01:47:00Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "exp_0013_v1",
      "questionId": "q_0013",
      "origin": "manual",
      "bodyEn": "This is true. The expressway passing lane is for overtaking. After passing, you should move back into the driving lane instead of staying in the passing lane.",
      "sourceDerived": true,
      "createdBy": "passdrive-editorial",
      "createdAt": "2026-03-12T01:50:00Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-03-12T01:51:00Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "exp_0014_v1",
      "questionId": "q_0014",
      "origin": "manual",
      "bodyEn": "This is true. Drivers are expected to yield to pedestrians, so pedestrian safety takes priority in everyday traffic situations.",
      "sourceDerived": true,
      "createdBy": "passdrive-editorial",
      "createdAt": "2026-03-12T01:54:00Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-03-12T01:55:00Z"
    }
  ],
